#: ../../../advanced_features/hisparse_guide.md:1
msgid "HiSparse: Hierarchical Sparse Attention"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/hisparse_guide.md:3
msgid ""
"HiSparse reduces per-request GPU memory consumption during the decode phase "
"by maintaining only a small \"hot\" KV buffer on GPU while keeping complete "
"KV data in CPU pinned memory. Combined with PD disaggregation, it enables "
"significantly higher decode concurrency."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/hisparse_guide.md:5
msgid ""
"**Prerequisites**: HiSparse only works with models that use **DeepSeek "
"Sparse Attention (DSA)**  architectures (e.g., DeepSeek-V3.2, GLM-5). These "
"models natively select a subset of tokens for attention, making it possible "
"to keep only the top-k KV on GPU while storing the full KV in host memory — "
"without accuracy loss.  Additionally, HiSparse currently requires **PD "
"disaggregation mode** and is enabled on the **decode instance** only."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/hisparse_guide.md:7
msgid "Why HiSparse?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/hisparse_guide.md:9
msgid ""
"In long-context LLM inference, each decoding request holds a full-length KV "
"cache on GPU, limiting the number of concurrent requests a decode instance "
"can serve. HiSparse addresses this by:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/hisparse_guide.md:11
msgid ""
"**Reducing GPU memory per request**: Each request occupies only a fixed-size "
"device buffer (e.g., 4KB tokens) instead of the full sequence length."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/hisparse_guide.md:12
msgid ""
"**On-demand swap-in**: A CUDA kernel dynamically loads the top-k most "
"relevant KV entries from host memory based on attention scores."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/hisparse_guide.md:13
msgid ""
"**Transparent to prefill**: HiSparse is entirely a decode-side optimization; "
"the prefill instance requires no changes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/hisparse_guide.md:15
msgid "Design Overview"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/hisparse_guide.md:17
msgid "Decode Workflow"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/hisparse_guide.md:19
msgid "Each decode step follows this flow:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/hisparse_guide.md:21
msgid "**Forward decode** — generate the next token"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/hisparse_guide.md:22
msgid ""
"**Top-k selection** — select the most relevant token positions via attention "
"scores"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/hisparse_guide.md:23
msgid ""
"**Swap-in** — the CUDA kernel loads top-k KV entries from host to device "
"buffer:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/hisparse_guide.md:24
msgid ""
"*Short sequences* (`seq_len ≤ device_buffer_size`): fast path, all KV "
"already in buffer"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/hisparse_guide.md:25
msgid ""
"*Long sequences*: hit detection → LRU reordering → miss handling (host → "
"device copy)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/hisparse_guide.md:26
msgid ""
"**Decode attention** — compute attention using the top-k device locations"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/hisparse_guide.md:27
msgid ""
"**Eager backup** — asynchronously copy the previous token's KV from device "
"to host"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/hisparse_guide.md:29
msgid "PD Disaggregation Integration (Direct-to-Host)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/hisparse_guide.md:31
msgid ""
"In PD disaggregation mode, the prefill instance transfers KV cache directly "
"into the decode instance's host pool via RDMA, bypassing the GPU entirely on "
"the decode side. This eliminates the transient GPU memory spike during KV "
"transfer and removes the staging DMA step."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/hisparse_guide.md:33
msgid ""
"Prefill GPU  ──RDMA──▶  Decode Host Pool (CPU pinned memory)\n"
"                              │\n"
"                              ▼\n"
"                     alloc device buffer (4KB)\n"
"                              │\n"
"                              ▼\n"
"                     swap-in kernel (on-demand top-k)\n"
msgstr ""

