#: ../../../advanced_features/hisparse_guide.md:121
msgid "Key Notes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/hisparse_guide.md:123
msgid ""
"The prefill instance does not need `--enable-hisparse`; it is unaware of "
"HiSparse."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/hisparse_guide.md:124
msgid ""
"On the decode instance, the following flags are **required** for HiSparse:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/hisparse_guide.md:125
msgid ""
"`--kv-cache-dtype bfloat16` — currently only bfloat16 KV cache is supported "
"(more dtypes planned)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/hisparse_guide.md:126
msgid ""
"`--nsa-decode-backend flashmla_sparse` — currently only `flashmla_sparse` "
"backend is supported."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/hisparse_guide.md:127
msgid "`--enable-hisparse` — enables HiSparse."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/hisparse_guide.md:128
msgid ""
"`--hisparse-config` — HiSparse configuration (top_k, device_buffer_size, "
"host_to_device_ratio)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/hisparse_guide.md:129
msgid ""
"`host_to_device_ratio` should be configured based on the host machine's "
"available memory. For example:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/hisparse_guide.md:130
msgid "**~1 TB** host memory → `host_to_device_ratio: 5`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/hisparse_guide.md:131
msgid "**~2 TB** host memory → `host_to_device_ratio: 10`"
msgstr ""

